\b \cf5 \strokec5 Origins
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 The earliest fandango melody is found in the anonymous "Libro de diferentes cifras de guitarra" from 1705, and the earliest description of the dance itself is found in a 1712 letter by Mart\'edn Mart\'ed, a Spanish priest. The fandango's first sighting in a theatrical work was in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Francisco_de_Leefadeal&action=edit&redlink=1"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \strokec6 Francisco de Leefadeal}}'s 
\i entrem\'e9s
\i0  "El novio de la aldeana" staged in Seville, ca. 1720. By the late 18th century it had become fashionable among the aristocracy and was often included in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tonadilla"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 tonadillas}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zarzuela"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 zarzuelas}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ballet"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 ballets}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opera"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 operas}}, not only in Spain, but also elsewhere in Europe.\
Widely varying claims have been made about the origin of fandango: its relation to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sole%C3%A1"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 sole\'e1}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Jabera&action=edit&redlink=1"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \strokec6 jabera}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petenera"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 petenera}}; to the Andalusian {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malague%C3%B1as_(flamenco_style)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 malague\'f1a}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Granadina&action=edit&redlink=1"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \strokec6 granadina}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Murciana&action=edit&redlink=1"}}{\fldrslt \cf6 \strokec6 murciana}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ronde%C3%B1a"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 ronde\'f1a}}; to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canary_dance"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 canario}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romani_people_in_Spain"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 gitano}}; to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jota_(music)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \strokec4 jota}} aragonesa.\
